The paper discusses the evolution of Web graph data technologies and emphasizes the need to extend the semantic Web standard stack. This involves knowledge representation, reasoning, and operationalization to model and support actors, actions, and interactions in web-based epistemic communities. These topics are closely related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI), databases (cs.DB), social networks (cs.SI), semantic web (cs.SW), and machine learning (cs.LG).
